Bodies of 22 people on board the plane that crashed into a mountainside in Nepal on Sunday, have been found from the wreckage, the Nepali news portal Kantipur Daily reported on Monday. The bodies will be taken to Nepal's capital Kathmandu. The Twin Otter plane, which was carrying 19 passengers and three crew members, including four Indians and two Germans, went missing on Sunday morning while flying from the city of Pokhara to the mountain town of Jomsom in Mustang district.